Key steps: 1. **Stopping at Step 2**: She stops if \( t_1 + t_2 > 1 \). The probability \( P(\text{stop at 2}) = \frac{1}{2} \). 2. **Stopping at Step 3**: She stops if \( t_1 + t_2 + t_3 > 1 \) after not stopping at steps 1 or 2. The probability \( P(\text{stop at 3}) = \frac{1}{3} \). 3. **Probability of Position > 1**: - Given she stops at step 2, \( P(x_1 + x_2 > 1) = \frac{1}{2} \). - Given she stops at step 3, \( P(x_1 + x_2 + x_3 > 1) = \frac{5}{6} \). Calculations: - Total probability: \[ P(\text{stop at 2}) \cdot P(x_1 + x_2 > 1) + P(\text{stop at 3}) \cdot P(x_1 + x_2 + x_3 > 1) \] \[ = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{3} \cdot \frac{5}{6} = \frac{1}{4} + \frac{5}{18} = \frac{9}{36} + \frac{10}{36} = \frac{19}{36} \] The numerator and denominator of the probability \(\frac{19}{36}\) are 19 and 36, respectively. Their sum is \(19 + 36 = 55\). \[ \boxed{55} \]
